President Cyril Ramaphosa is addressing the National Assembly this afternoon. He'll be answering questions as well as update the country on the progress of the COVID-19 vaccination programme.  * Editor's note: This live event has ended. You may watch a recording above. CAPE TOWN - President Cyril Ramaphosa will answer questions in the National Assembly on Thursday afternoon. The appearance comes at a time when the governing party is experiencing some challenges. READ: Magashule can't act unilaterally: Mabe On Wednesday, the ANC suspended its secretary-general Ace Magashule after he refused to step aside pending his fraud and corruption charges. In turn, Magashule issued a statement questioning his suspension and declaring President Ramaphosa suspended.